In the Matter of Malcolm S. ULRICH, Bankrupt-Appellant, Bridget Tuite, Creditor-Appellee. No. 223. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. March 21, 1938. David Tepp, of White Plains, N. Y., for bankrupt-appellant. Stephen R. J. Roach, of White Plains, N. Y., for appellee.

Before MANTON, L. HAND and AUGUSTUS N. HAND, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Order, 18 F.Supp. 919, affirmed.
